org.apache.beam.runners.dataflow

Class BlockingDataflowRunner

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.beam.sdk.runners.PipelineRunner<DataflowPipelineJob>
      • org.apache.beam.runners.dataflow.BlockingDataflowRunner

  • public class BlockingDataflowRunner
extends PipelineRunner<DataflowPipelineJob>
    A PipelineRunner that's like DataflowRunner but that waits for the launched job to finish.

    Logs job status updates and console messages while it waits.

    Returns the final job state, or throws an exception if the job fails or cannot be monitored.

    Permissions

    When reading from a Dataflow source or writing to a Dataflow sink using BlockingDataflowRunner, the Google cloud services account and the Google compute engine service account of the GCP project running the Dataflow Job will need access to the corresponding source/sink.

    Please see Google Cloud Dataflow Security and Permissions for more details.
